The first time I ate Boiling Crab here in Hawaii it was sooooo delicious. I ordered the crab and truly enjoyed the shrimp, clams, mussels, corn and sausage. The seasoning was so delicious I think I ordered the Shabang....garlicky with a kick it...so flavorful. But the next time I ordered, it wasn’t the same. The shrimp was mushy as if it was old. Like you could smash the shrimp with your finger. The first time i ordered it tasted so delicious so I said I have to give them one more try. I TRIED IT A THIRD TIME AND THE SHRIMP WAS INEDIBLE. Whatever the reason for the shrimp whether it was too old or overdone, it’s too much money to be spending on food only to be dissatisfied for a third time.  I hesitated when posting this I know how detrimental reviews can be to a small business so I waited a third time to post this before sharing. Don’t waist your time or money.

The Boiling Crab is one of several Cajun Seafood restaurants on Oahu that was all the rage a couple of years ago. A variety of seafood cooked in spicy Cajun sauces served by the pound, your meal is served in large bags which you then dump on the paper-lined table.  With plastic bibs around your necks, you dive into your Cajun care with your bare hands. Crawfish, clams, mussels, shrimp, sausages, corn and potatoes all cooked in a flavorful savory thick red sauce.  The staff here is always friendly and the vibe is more family-oriented than the other hipster spots at Salt. Parking is ample and free for the first hour, and a dollar for the next hour with validation.  All in all a nice place to fix your Cajun craving at a reasonable cost.
